HERE COMES THE FUN...
1. Do we know each other outside of Live Journal?
2. What's your philosophy on life?
3. Would you have my back in a fight?
4. Would you keep a secret from me if you thought it was in my best interest?
5. What is your favorite memory of us?
6. Would you give me a kidney?
7. Tell me one odd/interesting fact about you:
8. Would you take care of me when I'm sick?
9. Can we get together and make a cake?
10. Have you heard any rumors of me lately?
11. Do you/have you talk(ed) crap about me?
12. Do you think I'm a good person?
13. Would you drive across country with me?
14. Do you think I'm attractive?
15. If you could change anything about me, would you?
16. What do you wear to sleep?
17. Would you come over for no reason just to hang out?
18. Would you go on a date with me if i asked you?
19. If I only had one day to live, what would we do together?
20. Will you post this so I can fill it out for you?

Ok, lately i have been thinking about doing something and i am really not sure about the idea. So what do you think?
I am thinking about writing a book....a book about my life, or more so about what i think about my life in general and all the lessons i have learned along the way. Now the reason i say i am unsure is because i am not sure it would be interesting...on the other hand it does have alot of DRAMA!

Just throwing a thought out;)

Last Night was Halloween, so Dad and I (for some strange unknown reason) decided to go down to Sixth Street for the Big Halloween Party.... Pretty Interesting. Lots and lots of weirdos, mexicans, white trash, new orleans refugees and just plain weird college kids. We were really kind of disappointed at the lack of creativity in Austin of all places....We were down there for about 2 1/2 hours and only saw maybe a handful of creative original costumes. But there was absolutely no shortage of zombies, witches, pirates, and many variations of those oh so special "landscapers" LOL But Oh Least I Forget.....The SLUTS! OMG.....i was in shock at the things these girls were wearing....i mean i have been known to show some skin (haha) but no way in hell would i walk down any street wearing the things they were....Stacy and John would have had a great time together *wink* Ah but the best part of the night was knowing how many idiots in Austin will be wearing comfy houseshoes and bandaids for the next week...men and women...and all for the shoes! Anyway, here's a pic or two..... BTW..The first pic of Marie Antoinette was completely made of ouf newspaper...both of the costumes were... Love You, Momma
